<p>Cabos usados em pontes e linhas de transmiss√£o suportam o pr√≥prio peso uniformemente distribu√≠do e assumem um formato conhecido por <strong>caten√°ria</strong>, expresso por</p>

\[y(x) = a \cosh\left(\frac{x}{a}\right)\]

<p>sendo $a$ um comprimento definido na figura e</p>

\[\cosh \theta = \frac{e^\theta+e^{-\theta}}{2}\]

<p>a fun√ß√£o <strong>cosseno hiperb√≥lico</strong>.</p>

<p>Considere que o cabo est√° suspenso entre dois pontos distantes 100m um do outro, com uma m√°xima deflex√£o de 20m. Al√©m disso, o cabo tem um peso espec√≠fico de $w=50\,$N/m.</p>

<p>Determine as tens√µes m√≠nima e m√°xima suportadas pelo cabo, que  acontecem, respectivamente, no meio ($x=0$) e nas extremidades ($x = \pm 50\,$m) e s√£o dadas por $ T_\mathrm{min}= w a $ e $ T_\mathrm{max}= w (a+20)$.</p>


        
        

        <button class="btn btn-primary dropdown-toggle" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#catenaria" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="catenaria">
          Solu√ß√£o
        </button>
        <div class="collapse" id="catenaria">
          <div class="card card-body">
            

<p>A caten√°ria passa pelo ponto $x=50,\,y=a+20$, o que fornece a equa√ß√£o</p>

\[a+20 = a \cosh \left( \frac{50}{a} \right)\]

<p>que resolvemos numericamente:</p>

<div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">numpy</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">np</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">scipy.optimize</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">spo</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">f</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="p">):</span>  <span class="c1"># fun√ß√£o da qual se quer a raiz
</span>  <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">a</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">20</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">a</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">cosh</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">50</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">a</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">c</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">65</span>  <span class="c1"># chute inicial
</span><span class="n">a</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">spo</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">newton</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">c</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">w</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">50</span>
<span class="k">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">f'Tmin=</span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">w</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s">, Tmax=</span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">w</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s">'</span><span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Obtemos $a=65.5862\,$m. Com isso, as tens√µes m√≠nima e m√°xima s√£o</p>

\[T_\text{min} = \omega a = 3279.3\,\text{N}\]

\[T_\text{max} = \omega (a+20) = 4279.3\,\text{N}\]

          </div>
        </div>

        

    </div>
